            expandedText: '📖 **HTML semantics** means the element name carries meaning to browsers, search engines, and assistive technology. `<p>` signals a paragraph of prose, `<h1>` signals the primary heading, `<nav>` signals a navigation landmark — the visual appearance is secondary to this contract.\n\n🔬 A screen reader user, a search engine crawler, and a sighted browser user all depend on correct element choice. Choosing `<div>` instead of `<button>` loses keyboard accessibility and ARIA semantics simultaneously. The element name is the most important decision you make.',
