            expandedText: '📖 Tag names are defined in the **HTML Living Standard** maintained by WHATWG. The browser maps each tag name to an implicit ARIA role — `<button>` gets `role="button"`, `<a href>` gets `role="link"`, `<nav>` gets `role="navigation"`. This role determines what assistive technology announces without any extra ARIA markup.\n\n📖 Void elements like `<img>`, `<input>`, `<br>`, and `<hr>` have no closing tag because they have no content model — they represent external resources or layout breaks with no children.',
