            expandedText: '📖 There must be **only one `<main>` element** per page. It maps to ARIA `role="main"` and is the target of "skip to main content" links — a WCAG accessibility requirement that lets keyboard users bypass repeated navigation elements.\n\n📖 `<article>` represents self-contained content that could be independently distributed or syndicated — a blog post, a forum post, a product card. Each `<article>` can have its own `<header>` and `<footer>`. `<section>` groups thematically related content but is not independently distributable — it always needs its surrounding context.',
            codeExample: '<main>\n  <article>\n    <h2>Post Title</h2>\n    <p>Content here…</p>\n  </article>\n</main>',
