            animationStep: 5,
            icon: '📦',
            heading: 'section, aside, and figure',
            text: '`<section>` groups related content with its own heading — a chapter within a main area. `<aside>` holds tangentially related content: a sidebar, a pull quote, a related links panel. `<figure>` groups media with `<figcaption>` — the caption visually and semantically describes the figure.',
            expandedText: '📖 `<section>` should always contain a **heading** (`<h2>` through `<h6>`) because it represents a thematic grouping that should be nameable. Without a heading, `<section>` provides no more semantic value than `<div>`.\n\n📖 `<figure>` and `<figcaption>` create an association between an image (or code block, or diagram) and its caption. The caption is optional — `<figure>` without `<figcaption>` is valid when no caption is needed but the content is a standalone illustration. Both elements are block-level; `<figcaption>` must be the first or last child of `<figure>`.',
            codeExample: '<main>\n  <section aria-labelledby="intro-heading">\n    <h2 id="intro-heading">Introduction</h2>\n    <p>Content here...</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <aside>\n    <h2>Related articles</h2>\n    <ul>...</ul>\n  </aside>\n</main>\n\n<figure>\n  <img src="chart.png" alt="Bar chart of monthly sales">\n  <figcaption>Figure 1: Monthly sales Q1 2026</figcaption>\n</figure>',
            language: 'html',
