            expandedText: '📖 External stylesheets are **cached** by the browser after the first download — returning visitors pay no network cost. The browser uses the `ETag` or `Last-Modified` headers to validate the cached version. Long cache lifetimes combined with content-addressed filenames (like `style.abc123.css` from a build tool) are a standard performance optimization.\n\n📖 A single external stylesheet can be applied across an entire website, ensuring visual consistency without duplication. CSS preprocessors like Sass and Less compile to a single CSS file. Build tools like Vite bundle multiple CSS files into one, minimizing HTTP requests.',
