            heading: 'Padding',
          icon: '🔲',
            text: 'Padding is the space between your content and the border — it is interior breathing room that belongs to the element. Because it is inside the border, padding inherits the element\'s background color, visually extending the colored area. Use shorthand to set all four sides at once: `padding: 16px` (all sides), `padding: 8px 16px` (top/bottom, left/right).',
            expandedText: '⚠️ Padding is rendered with the **element background color**, so it visually extends the colored area of the element. A common pattern is setting `padding` on a container to create internal breathing room rather than applying `margin` on child elements, which avoids margin collapse edge cases.\n\n✅ Padding shorthand follows the **TRBL (Top Right Bottom Left)** clockwise convention: `padding: 10px 20px 10px 20px` sets top, right, bottom, left. Two-value shorthand `padding: 10px 20px` sets top/bottom and left/right. One value sets all four sides equally. Individual sides: `padding-top`, `padding-right`, `padding-bottom`, `padding-left`.',
