            expandedText: '📖 Borders are drawn on top of the background and inside the **CSS outline**. With the default `content-box` sizing, borders add to the total element size. With `border-box`, borders are included in the declared `width` and `height`. The `outline` property (used for focus indicators) does not affect layout — it renders outside the border without pushing other elements.\n\n📖 Border shorthand (`border: 2px solid #333`) sets all four sides. Individual sides (`border-top`, `border-right`, etc.) override specific edges. `border-radius` rounds corners independently or uniformly. Setting `border-radius: 50%` on a square element creates a circle.',
