            expandedText: 'The classic centering solution: display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center on the container. justify-content aligns along the main axis (horizontal by default); align-items aligns along the cross axis (vertical by default). Together they center children in both directions.\n\nThis replaces the old techniques of margin: auto (horizontal only), display: table-cell; vertical-align: middle (verbose), and the notorious negative margin + transform hack. For single-element centering in a full-page layout: min-height: 100vh; display: flex; justify-content: center; align-items: center on body. For centering text within a button: display: inline-flex keeps the button inline while centering its content.',
