            expandedText: '📖 The modern CSS Color Level 4 `color()` syntax can express **P3 wide-gamut colors** that go beyond sRGB. `color(display-p3 1 0 0)` is a more vibrant red than `#ff0000` on P3 displays (modern Apple devices). The `@supports` rule detects support: `@supports (color: color(display-p3 1 0 0))`.\n\n📖 The 4-argument `rgb()` (modern CSS Color 4 syntax) and `rgba()` are now equivalent: `rgb(255 0 0 / 50%)` and `rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.5)` produce identical results in all modern browsers. The space-separated syntax is the newer standard.',
