            heading: 'font-family, font-size, font-weight',
          icon: '🔤',
            text: '`font-family` sets the typeface — always end with a generic fallback. `font-size` controls how big text appears. `font-weight` ranges from 100 (thin) to 900 (black), with 400 = normal and 700 = bold.',
            expandedText: '📖 The **font-family cascade** means the browser tries each listed family in order, using the first one available. Generic families (`sans-serif`, `serif`, `monospace`) are the mandatory final fallback — every browser guarantees at least one font for each.\n\n📖 System font stacks like `-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif` use the operating system\'s native font for a familiar appearance with zero download cost. Variable fonts provide all weights and styles in a single file — `@font-face` with `format("woff2-variations")` enables fine-grained weight control across the 100–900 range.',
