            expandedText: '📖 Using a **unitless line-height** (like 1.6) is critical for inheritance. `line-height: 24px` on a parent does not scale when a child increases its font-size — lines overlap. `line-height: 1.6` means "1.6 times the current font-size" and scales automatically throughout the inheritance chain.\n\n📖 Typography guidelines for body text: `font-size: 16px–18px`, `line-height: 1.5–1.7`, `max-width: 65ch–75ch`. The `ch` unit equals the width of the "0" character, making it ideal for controlling line length. Research shows lines longer than 75 characters reduce reading comprehension.',
