          icon: '🌍',
            text: 'Load custom fonts with `@import` or `<link>` at the top of your CSS. Google Fonts generates the URL for you. `@font-face` works the same way but for self-hosted files. Add `display=swap` to show a fallback font immediately while the web font loads, preventing invisible text.',
            expandedText: '📖 The `display=swap` descriptor in `@font-face` (and the corresponding URL parameter in Google Fonts) tells the browser to show a **fallback font** immediately, then swap to the web font when loaded. This prevents FOIT (Flash of Invisible Text). `font-display: optional` is better for performance — if the font is not cached and cannot load quickly, the fallback is used permanently for that page load.\n\n⚠️ Self-hosting fonts avoids third-party DNS lookups and connection overhead. Build tools can **subset** fonts to only the characters used in the page, dramatically reducing file size. Variable fonts provide all weights in a single file, further reducing HTTP requests.',
            codeExample: '/* At top of CSS file */\n@import url("https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;700&display=swap");\n\nbody { font-family: "Inter", sans-serif; }',
