            expandedText: '✅ Pattern **wildcards** provide flexible matching. `*` matches any string within a single path component (not across `/`); `**` matches any number of path components: `**/logs` matches `logs/`, `build/logs/`, and `packages/api/logs/`. `?` matches any single character. Negation with `!` un-ignores a pattern: `!src/generated-important-file.ts` re-includes a file excluded by a broader pattern.\n\n✅ A common pattern for Node.js projects: ignore `node_modules/`, the `dist/` or `build/` directory, `.env` files but allow `.env.example`, log files, and OS metadata files. GitHub provides a collection of standard `.gitignore` templates at `github.com/github/gitignore` for every language and framework. Running `npx gitignore node` generates the standard Node.js `.gitignore` using the gitignore.io API.',
